<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/7ae7708cdefae776775d819676794964.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 2 and c = 7. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
A = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place. Give angles in <em>degrees</em>.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>6.7</li><li>16.6</li><li>73.4</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}^{{2}}={2}^{{2}}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{49}={4}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{49}-{4}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{45}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle\sqrt{{{45}}}={b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{6.7082039324994}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{6.7}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle A</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arcsin{{\left(\frac{{2}}{{7}}\right)}}}\approx{16.601549599003}\approx{16.6}</m></p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arccos{{\left(\frac{{2}}{{7}}\right)}}}\approx{73.398450400997}\approx{73.4}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

